    <p>In this work the authors present a pipeline implemented in Nextflow for the analysis of CLIP-Seq datasets. CLIP-Seq is widely used to capture RNA-binding protein interactions with their target genes. However, the analysis of CLIP-Seq datasets can be challenging especially for non-experts in the field. The development of pipelines, besides facilitating analysis, provide the added benefit of increased reproducibility and correctness. Overall, the tool is nicely described, and the pipeline is well designed. Nextflow and nf-core are stable platforms that facilitate customization and deployment on diverse hardware environments. It will be important that the authors maintain and support the software in the long-term. This tool will be helpful to the community, will facilitate the analysis of CLIP-Seq data and will increase research reproducibility.</p>
